cs.FL, cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with tree languages and automata theory.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely as the paper discusses the complexity of languages in Cantor space, which is related to mathematical logic.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the topological complexity of languages, which is related to computational complexity.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with constructing languages using a building block.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses the complexity of languages in the context of nondeterministic automata, which is related to game theory.
